node.title: London 'Million Mask March' protesters burn effigy of Boris Johnson, set off fireworks
node.alt: A crowd of people walk around a square as bright fireworks soar into the night sky, illuminating nearby buidlings.
node.description: The anti-capitalist event coincides with Guy Fawkes celebrations in the UK, with many of the protesters wearing masks bearing the face of the man behind the gunpowder plot of 1605.
node.content:
["Twelve people have been arrested in London amid late-night clashes with police during the so-called Million Mask March.", "Hundreds of anti-capitalist protestors\u00a0gathered in London's Parliament Square and fireworks were thrown at police officers as tensions rose.", "", "
Protesters against austerity and the infringement of rights also gathered in London's\u00a0Trafalgar Square.(AP: Kirsty Wigglesworth)
", "Eight officers were injured at the protest, London's Metropolitan Police said on Twitter.", "The Met condemned the offences and said the injuries were \"unacceptable\".", "
Former Labour leader's brother spits fire
", "", "
An effigy of Britain's Prime Minister Boris Johnson burns in Trafalgar Square.(AP: Kirsty Wigglesworth)
", "Earlier in the evening, demonstrators wearing Guy Fawkes-style masks burned an effigy of UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson.", "Protesters\u00a0were also entertained by local activist Piers Corbyn \u2014 brother of former Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn and well-known opposition figure \u2014 who gave them a fire-breathing display.", "An eyewitness video showed Mr Corbyn\u00a0spitting fire while surrounded by a crowd holding anti-government signs.", "", "
The masks worn by some of the protesters pay tribute to the man behind a failed 1605 plot to assassinate King James I.
", "The anti-capitalist event coincides with Guy Fawkes celebrations in the UK, with many of the protesters wearing masks bearing the face of the man behind the gunpowder plot of 1605.", "The masks are synonymous with hacking group Anonymous and featured prominently in the V for Vendetta movie.", "", "
Demonstrations were organised by activist group Anonymous.(AFP: Rasid Necati Aslim/Anadolu Agency)
", "ABC/Wires"]
